title: Extracted Features
description: The Extracted Features (EF) dataset contains features derived for every page of 13.6 million volumes in HathiTrust, including part-of-speech tagged token counts, header and footer identification, and various line-level information.

title: Linguistic Data Consortium (LDC) corpora
rights: Data may be reused by affiliates of Rutgers University only for non-commercial education, research and technology development purposes only.
publisher: SALTS Lab: Laboratory for the Study of Applied Language Technology and Society
description: A collection of linguistic corpora that includes sources as varied as newswire text data, research articles, emails, and telephone conversations.

title: Spectator
subject: Culture
description: The Spectator (1711-14), by Joseph Addison and Richard Steele, was an extremely innovative publication; it was enormously influential, not only in the content of its speculations on aesthetics, literary style, and urban life, but also as a medium.

title: Peter Still Papers
subject: Slavery; African Americans
description: Correspondence (1850-1875), chiefly relating to Still's campaign to purchase his wife, Vina Still, and family held as slaves in Alabama and the publication (1856) of Kate E. R. Picard's biography, The Kidnapped and the Ransomed; memo book (1853-1854) of funds collected; and Still family record (1798-1821). Persons and places represented include William Lloyd Garrison, Horace Greeley, Harriet Beecher Stowe, and Cortlandt Van Rensselaer, and Burlington, NJ, and Philadelphia, PA. 57 items.

title: Medical Society of New Jersey publications
subject: history of medicine
description: The New Jersey Medical Reporter was founded in 1847 by Dr. Joseph Parrish, and was published in Burlington, N.J. from 1847 to 1857. Historian of medicine David Cowen considered the Reporter to be Â“the first professional journal of substance in New Jersey.Â”

title: New Jersey College of Medicine and Dentistry medical school site hearings
subject: history of Newark; history of medicine
description: Transcripts of public hearings held in February and March of 1968 regarding the establishment of a proposed medical school in Newark, soon to become the New Jersey College of Medicine and Dentistry.

title: New Jersey health statistics
subject: history of New Jersey; history of medicine
description: This compendium is an enormous archive of official annual reports on the health of New Jersey, including extensive compilations of population-based health statistics, which covers over 45,000 pages of original content in the 141 separate documents that it incorporates.

title: Network datasets
description: A list of open online repositories of network datasets, collected by Katherine Ognyanova of Rutgers SC&I.
